SHIGELLOSIS, SUMMER CAMP - RUSSIA (KALININGRAD)
***********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
See Also
Shigellosis - Russia (Udmurtia) 2000.0025
Date: 24 July 2000
From: Vladyko A. <vladyko@ns.briem.ac.by>
ProMED-mail Regional Moderator for NIS/CIS
Source: Official information from the Health Ministry of the Russian
Federation <http://www.depart.drugreg.ru/hotline/index.html> (Outbreaks
News Website, in Russian) 10 Jul 2000 [edited

Dysentery - Russia (Kaliningrad province)
------------------------------------------
In the summer camp "Ogonyek" (for 235 children) in Svetlogorsk City,
Kaliningrad province (oblast) 49 cases (48 of them - children) of acute
intestinal infection were registered beginning from 8-10 Jul 2000. All
patients have been hospitalised, 4 of them in serious condition, the rest
have a middle-serious and light forms of the
disease. The dysentery infectious agent _Shigella sonnei_ has been isolated
from the specimens of 12 patients. Supposedly, the outbreak is foodborne
and connected with use of a ready dish, infected in the camp kitchen. The
source and mode of infectious transmission are being investigated.
Specialists from the Center of the State
Sanitary-Epidemiological Surveillance in Kaliningrad province, and Health
Ministry organisation are involved in the epidemiological investigation.
Appropriate containment measures have been instituted.
